y linked. The first anthology to provide a worldwide perspective on the birth and development of the field, A Global History of Sexual Science contends that actors outside of Europe-in Asia, Latin America, and Africa-became important interlocutors in debates on prostitution, birth control, and transvestism. Ideas circulated through intellectual exchange, travel, and internationally produced and disseminated publications. Twenty scholars tackle specific issues, including the female orgasm and the criminalization of male homosexuality, to demonstrate how concepts and ideas introduced by sexual scientists gained currency throughout the modern world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aSexologyxHistoryy19th century. 0aSexologyxHistoryy20th century. 70(DE-601)1060803420(DE-588)4077394-2aSexualwissenschaft2gnd 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh1 aFuechtner, Veronika, eeditor.1 aHaynes, Douglas E., eeditor.1 aJones, Ryan M., eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520966673423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520966673.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles